What you need to know:  Kenya Simba coach Odera reckons that the skill-set, versatility and guile of the much praised Kubu at fly half position is just what Kenya needed in their World Cup qualifier campaignThe Fijian-born rugby player first came to Kenya in 2014 with Samurai International for the Safari Sevens and was the convinced to stay by Kabras Sugar Rugby thinking he would be in the country for a short stint only to, not only stay longer, but get citizenship and become a key figure in the national team set-up